31/01/2006
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska (RS) President Dragan Cavic opens political consultations Tuesday (31 January) aimed at nominating a new prime minister-designate and issuing a mandate for forming a new government in the entity. 
According to a statement from Cavic's cabinet, the president will hold separate talks with the various parties in parliament by the end of this week. 
Last week, the government of the Serb Democratic Party was removed from office after a successful no confidence vote, initiated by the main opposition Union of Independent Social Democrats and backed by minor opposition parties. 
(Nezavisne novine - 31/01/06; RTRS, Fena - 30/01/06)
